      </nav>

      <!-- Layout Grid: Left Content (Prose), Right Sticky Table of Contents -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-12 relative z-10">
        
        <!-- Main Article Body (Prose) -->
        <article class="lg:col-span-8 bg-white border border-slate-200/80 rounded-3xl p-6 sm:p-10 lg:p-12 shadow-xs max-w-none">
          
          <!-- Article Header -->
          <header class="border-b border-slate-100 pb-8 mb-8">
            <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-md bg-indigo-50 px-2.5 py-1 text-xs font-bold text-indigo-700 mb-4">
              Productivity Stack
            </span>
            <h1 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-slate-900 tracking-tight leading-[1.15] mb-6">
              Best AI Note-Taking Apps in 2026: The Ultimate Guide
            </h1>
            
            <!-- Author Card -->
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <div class="h-10 w-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-600 text-indigo-50 flex items-center justify-center font-display text-sm font-bold shadow-sm">
                IP
              </div>
              <div class="text-xs">
                <p class="font-bold text-slate-800">Imperial Picks Editorial Team</p>
                <p class="text-slate-400 font-medium mt-0.5">Published on June 11, 2026 • 18 min read</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </header>

          <!-- Introduction Section -->
          <section id="introduction" class="prose max-w-[72ch]">
            <h2 class="sr-only">Introduction</h2>
            <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-600 leading-relaxed font-medium mb-6">
              The nature of human knowledge management has undergone a fundamental paradigm shift. For decades, note-taking apps were digital versions of paper notebooks—static folders, subfolders, and manual tags that required constant, disciplined maintenance. If you neglected your filing system for a month, your knowledge base became a chaotic digital graveyard where useful ideas were lost forever.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
              In 2026, artificial intelligence has completely reimagined this relationship. Note-taking tools are no longer passive repositories; they have evolved into active intellectual partners. Powered by semantic search, Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG), and localized vector databases, modern note apps automatically structure your ideas, connect distant concepts, summarize complex meetings, and allow you to hold real-time conversations with your own collective memory.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
              However, the explosion of AI-enhanced productivity tools has introduced a new problem: choice overload. Every note app claims to be 'AI-first', but their implementations vary wildly. Some rely on simple, expensive OpenAI API wrappers that summarize paragraphs. Others offer local, offline LLMs that preserve absolute data privacy, or source-grounded research chambers that analyze hundreds of pages of academic literature with zero hallucinations. 
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
              To help you build a reliable personal knowledge base, the Imperial Picks Editorial Team has spent months auditing, structuring, and testing the leading tools in real-world scenarios. We skip the marketing sponsorships to bring you an honest, detailed guide comparing the six best AI note-taking applications on the market today.
            </p>

            <!-- Callout: Trust & Data Integrity -->
            <div class="border-l-4 border-indigo-500 bg-indigo-50/50 p-5 rounded-r-2xl mb-8">
              <div class="flex gap-2">
                <span class="text-lg">🛡️</span>
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-bold text-indigo-900 text-sm">Unbiased Editorial Standard</h4>
                  <p class="text-xs text-indigo-800 leading-relaxed mt-1">
                    At Imperial Picks, we test software ourselves. This review contains no affiliate links, sponsored scores, or automated comparisons. We evaluate apps based on data portability, offline access, search accuracy, formatting control, and pricing transparency.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- Quick Comparison Table -->
          <section id="comparison-table" class="mt-12 scroll-mt-20">
            <h2 class="font-display text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 tracking-tight mb-6 pb-2 border-b border-slate-100">
              Quick Comparison: AI Note-Taking Apps
            </h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
              The table below summarizes the key trade-offs in features, pricing structures, and core AI capabilities among the top note-taking applications in 2026.
            </p>
            
            <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50/50 p-1 mb-8">
              <table class="w-full text-left text-sm border-collapse bg-white rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
                <thead>
                  <tr class="bg-slate-900 text-white font-display text-xs uppercase tracking-wider">
                    <th class="py-4 px-4 font-semibold">App</th>
                    <th class="py-4 px-4 font-semibold">Best For</th>
                    <th class="py-4 px-4 font-semibold">Free Plan</th>
                    <th class="py-4 px-4 font-semibold">Starting Price</th>
                    <th class="py-4 px-4 font-semibold">AI Features</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-100 text-slate-700">
                  <tr class="hover:bg-slate-50/80 transition-colors">
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 font-bold text-slate-900">Notion AI</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4">Database organization & wiki pages</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4">
                      <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-md bg-emerald-50 px-2 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-emerald-800 border border-emerald-200/50">Yes (Core Notion free)</span>
                    </td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 font-semibold text-slate-900">+$10/month add-on</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 text-xs">Global Q&A, Database Autofill, Inline Editor</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr class="hover:bg-slate-50/80 transition-colors">
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 font-bold text-slate-900">Mem AI</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4">Folderless unstructured quick capture</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4">
                      <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-md bg-emerald-50 px-2 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-emerald-800 border border-emerald-200/50">Yes (Basic capture)</span>
                    </td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 font-semibold text-slate-900">$8/month</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 text-xs">Semantic linking, Smart Mem Chat, Folderless organization</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr class="hover:bg-slate-50/80 transition-colors">
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 font-bold text-slate-900">Obsidian + AI</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4">Local-first data privacy & custom structures</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4">
                      <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-md bg-emerald-50 px-2 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-emerald-800 border border-emerald-200/50">Yes (100% Free)</span>
                    </td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 font-semibold text-slate-900">Free (Own API keys)</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 text-xs">Vector Search plugins, local LLM sync (Ollama), canvas AI</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr class="hover:bg-slate-50/80 transition-colors">
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 font-bold text-slate-900">OneNote Copilot</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4">Microsoft 365 canvas & corporate ecosystem</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4">
                      <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-md bg-rose-50 px-2 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-rose-800 border border-rose-200/50">No (Paid Office plan)</span>
                    </td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 font-semibold text-slate-900">+$20-$30/month</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 text-xs">Handwriting to text, voice notes summary, Office integration</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr class="hover:bg-slate-50/80 transition-colors">
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 font-bold text-slate-900">Evernote AI</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4">OCR scanning, PDF storage & simple cleanup</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4">
                      <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-md bg-rose-50 px-2 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-rose-800 border border-rose-200/50">Limited (50 Notes)</span>
                    </td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 font-semibold text-slate-900">$14.99/month</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 text-xs">AI Search across OCR files, formatting cleanup tool</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr class="hover:bg-slate-50/80 transition-colors">
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 font-bold text-slate-900">NotebookLM</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4">Academic document research & podcast creation</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4">
                      <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-md bg-emerald-50 px-2 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-emerald-800 border border-emerald-200/50">Yes (100% Free)</span>
                    </td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 font-semibold text-slate-900">Free</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 text-xs">Grounded RAG references, Audio podcast summaries, PDF study guides</td>
                  </tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- Detailed Reviews Section -->
          <section id="detailed-reviews" class="mt-16 space-y-20">
            <h2 class="font-display text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 tracking-tight pb-2 border-b border-slate-100">
              Detailed Reviews: The Top 6 AI Note-Taking Apps
            </h2>

            <!-- Review: Notion AI -->
            <div id="tool-notion" class="scroll-mt-20">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                <span class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-purple-50 text-purple-600 border border-purple-100 font-bold font-display">01</span>
                <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-extrabold text-slate-900">Notion AI: The Database Powerhouse</h3>
              </div>
              
              <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                Notion has long been the gold standard for workspace wikis, study trackers, and database structures. By integrating AI directly into its block editor, Notion has turned database rows and paragraphs into dynamic elements. Instead of just searching for text, you can ask Notion AI to write formulas, create summaries of meetings, compile action items, or pull answers from your entire history of pages.
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                The defining feature of Notion AI is its database integration. You can add a column named "AI Summary" or "AI Translation" to any database, write a single prompt, and the platform will automatically run the AI query on every row, updating hundreds of entries simultaneously.
              </p>

              <h4 class="font-display text-sm font-bold text-slate-800 mb-3">Key Features</h4>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mb-6 text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-2">
                <li><strong>Workspace Q&A:</strong> Ask a natural language question in the sidebar, and Notion AI will search all your workspace pages (and connected integrations like Slack and Google Drive) to return a synthesized answer with links.</li>
                <li><strong>Database Autofill:</strong> Set AI prompts to automatically summarize transcripts, extract keywords, or translate articles in tabular rows.</li>
                <li><strong>Inline Text Assistant:</strong> Press spacebar anywhere on a blank page to trigger drafting, editing, tone shifting, or formatting improvements.</li>
              </ul>

              <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
                <!-- Pros -->
                <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl bg-emerald-50/30 border border-emerald-100">
                  <h4 class="font-display font-bold text-emerald-950 text-sm mb-3">✓ Advantages</h4>
                  <ul class="list-disc pl-4 space-y-2 text-xs text-emerald-800">
                    <li>Deep database automation saves hours of manual content curation.</li>
                    <li>Global Q&A connects your personal wiki with Google Drive and Slack.</li>
                    <li>Excellent collaboration tools for team project management.</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
                <!-- Cons -->
                <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl bg-rose-50/30 border border-rose-100">
                  <h4 class="font-display font-bold text-rose-950 text-sm mb-3">✗ Disadvantages</h4>
                  <ul class="list-disc pl-4 space-y-2 text-xs text-rose-800">
                    <li>AI subscription ($10/month) is an add-on on top of standard premium plans.</li>
                    <li>Cannot run local/offline models; requires a stable cloud connection.</li>
                    <li>Highly structured database layouts have a steep learning curve.</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- Callout: Notion AI Details -->
              <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50/50 p-5 space-y-3 text-sm">
                <p><strong>Pricing:</strong> Core Notion is free. Notion AI is a subscription add-on costing $10/user/month (or $8/user/month if billed annually).</p>
                <p><strong>Best Use Cases:</strong> Managing comprehensive databases, corporate knowledge bases, course syllabi, and structured weekly agendas.</p>
                <p><strong>Verdict:</strong> Choose Notion AI if you already use databases to organize your life and need an assistant to search, summarize, and link your records automatically.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Review: Mem AI -->
            <div id="tool-mem" class="scroll-mt-20 border-t border-slate-100 pt-12">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                <span class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-indigo-50 text-indigo-600 border border-indigo-100 font-bold font-display">02</span>
                <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-extrabold text-slate-900">Mem AI: The Self-Organizing Workspace</h3>
              </div>
              
              <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                Mem AI approach to note-taking is built on a simple premise: human organization is inefficient. Instead of forcing users to build folder trees, construct tags, or manage links, Mem provides a flat, timeline-based feed where you capture raw text. Behind the scenes, Mem's graph neural networks and vector database analyze your notes and link them conceptually.
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                As you type a note about a new client or meeting, a sidebar dynamically surfaces related notes from years ago. You don't have to search for them; the system understands the context and brings relevant information to you.
              </p>

              <h4 class="font-display text-sm font-bold text-slate-800 mb-3">Key Features</h4>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mb-6 text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-2">
                <li><strong>Zero-Folder Semantic Search:</strong> Finds files based on conceptual meaning. Searching for "ideas for our next campaign" will retrieve notes that discuss marketing plans, even if they don't contain the exact phrase.</li>
                <li><strong>Mem Chat:</strong> A localized chat assistant that answers questions based exclusively on your past notes, acting as a personal search query engine.</li>
                <li><strong>Smart Suggestions:</strong> A real-time sidebar that surfaces past ideas, related people, and matching drafts as you compose new notes.</li>
              </ul>

              <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
                <!-- Pros -->
                <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl bg-emerald-50/30 border border-emerald-100">
                  <h4 class="font-display font-bold text-emerald-950 text-sm mb-3">✓ Advantages</h4>
                  <ul class="list-disc pl-4 space-y-2 text-xs text-emerald-800">
                    <li>Completely eliminates folder and tag management overhead.</li>
                    <li>Highly effective at bubbling up forgotten connections between older notes.</li>
                    <li>Fast and simple quick-capture interface for raw thoughts.</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
                <!-- Cons -->
                <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl bg-rose-50/30 border border-rose-100">
                  <h4 class="font-display font-bold text-rose-950 text-sm mb-3">✗ Disadvantages</h4>
                  <ul class="list-disc pl-4 space-y-2 text-xs text-rose-800">
                    <li>No database features or custom layout settings.</li>
                    <li>Hard to navigate manually if you prefer visual hierarchy or folders.</li>
                    <li>Requires trust in black-box AI organization algorithms.</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- Callout: Mem AI Details -->
              <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50/50 p-5 space-y-3 text-sm">
                <p><strong>Pricing:</strong> Free basic plan with manual search. Mem Premium costs $8/month (billed annually) for unlimited AI chat, semantic links, and full storage sync.</p>
                <p><strong>Best Use Cases:</strong> Quick thoughts, daily logs, meeting transcripts, and individuals who want a friction-free knowledge log.</p>
                <p><strong>Verdict:</strong> The absolute best choice for creators and busy executives who write daily journals and want an AI assistant to organize and search their notes automatically.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Review: Obsidian + AI Plugins -->
            <div id="tool-obsidian" class="scroll-mt-20 border-t border-slate-100 pt-12">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                <span class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-orange-50 text-orange-600 border border-orange-100 font-bold font-display">03</span>
                <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-extrabold text-slate-900">Obsidian + Community AI: The Private Knowledge Graph</h3>
              </div>
              
              <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                Obsidian is a local-first markdown note-taking tool that stores all files directly on your device. While the core team avoids locking users into proprietary AI models, Obsidian's massive community has built plugins that turn it into a highly powerful, private AI assistant. 
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                Using plugins like <em>Smart Connections</em> or <em>Copilot for Obsidian</em>, you can create vector embeddings of your local folder structures. You can connect these plugins to OpenAI's API, Anthropic's API, or run offline language models (like Llama 3 or Mistral) locally via Ollama. This setup ensures that your notes remain fully private and functional even without an internet connection.
              </p>

              <h4 class="font-display text-sm font-bold text-slate-800 mb-3">Key Features</h4>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mb-6 text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-2">
                <li><strong>Local Vector Embeddings:</strong> Plugins index your local Markdown folder, allowing you to search your notes semantically and chat with your files offline.</li>
